# Prepositions Reference Content

Connecting words and their case requirements - location, direction, and relationships.

## Purpose

Show how prepositions work in Greek, with special focus on the σε contraction and the "Big Four" prepositions that cover 90%+ of usage.

## Key Insight

All Greek prepositions take accusative case. The Big Four (σε, από, για, με) cover most situations.

---

## Decision Navigator

<decision-guide name="preposition-selection">
<question>Which preposition do I need?</question>

| Question              | Answer    | Examples                              |
|-----------------------|-----------|---------------------------------------|
| Where is it / going TO? | σε → στο | Πάω στο σπίτι (going home)           |
| Where FROM?           | από       | Είμαι από την Ελλάδα (from Greece)   |
| WITH whom/what?       | με        | Καφέ με γάλα (with milk)             |
| FOR whom/purpose?     | για       | Αυτό είναι για σένα (for you)        |

</decision-guide>

