## Prepositions with Pronouns

<section name="prep-pronouns">
<rule>After prepositions, use emphatic (long) pronoun forms</rule>
<why>Short pronouns (με, σε) go BEFORE verbs. After prepositions, you need the emphatic forms.</why>

| Greek         | English      |
|---------------|--------------|
| για μένα      | for me       |
| με σένα       | with you     |
| από αυτόν     | from him     |
| χωρίς εμάς    | without us   |
| μαζί σου      | with you (together) |

</section>

